p:
The seed of this plant is used in ancient medicine for a number of ailments including back pain, asthma, fever, bronchitis, cough, chest congestion, dizziness, paralysis, chronic headache, inflammation, infertility, and other gastrointestinal disorders like dyspepsia, flatulence, diarrhea, and dysentery (
 Durmuskahya and Ozturk, 2013; 
 Gholamnezhad et al., 2016; 
 Nasir et al., 2014; 
 Shah, 1966). Additionally, 
 N. sativa seed oil is used for the remedy of an abscess, nasal ulcer, swollen joint, orchitis and eczema. 
 N. sativa oil is also used in combination with honey for asthmatic problems, bronchospasms and chest congestion (
 Gholamnezhad et al., 2016; 
 Nasir et al., 2014). In ancient literature, 
 N. sativa is also attributed as an analgesic, liver tonic, diuretic, appetite stimulant, analgesic and digestive (
 Gilani et al., 2004; 
 Rajsekhar and Kuldeep, 2011; 
 Tavakkoli et al., 2017; 
 Ziaee et al., 2012).
